annotationA: Fatty acyl-CoA reductase wat; Catalyzes the reduction of saturated fatty acyl-CoA to fatty alcohols. The preferred substrates are C24:0 and C26:0. Necessary for the final stages of tracheal maturation, to facilitate the transition from water-filled to gas-filled tubes. May help to maintain the integrity of the outer hydrophobic envelope of the trachea
annotationB: Translation factor waclaw, mitochondrial; Promotes mitochondrial protein synthesis. May act as a fidelity factor of the translation reaction, by catalyzing a one- codon backward translocation of tRNAs on improperly translocated ribosomes. Binds to mitochondrial ribosomes in a GTP-dependent manner
